<span class="hljs-tag">&lt;/<span class="hljs-title">form</span>&gt;</span></pre>
            <h2 class="cd-text cd-title">example short form</h2>
            <p class="cd-text">Some forms are only small and suitable for a single line. Inputs line up with buttons for that reason. Use the <a href="http://pistachio.graze.com/basics/grid-system#bootstrap-grid">bootstrap grid classes</a> to achieve this. Inspect the example markup below for an example.</p>
            <form method="get" action="javascript:void(0);">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xxs-12">
            <label for="email-short">signup to our newsletter</label>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group col-xs-8">
            <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email-short" name="email" required placeholder="example@address.com">
        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-4">
            <button class="button button--primary button--continue button--block" type="submit">sign up</button>
        </div>
    </div>
</form>
<pre class="hljs xml"><span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-title">form</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">method</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"get"</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">action</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"javascript:void(0);"</span>&gt;</span>
    <span class="hljs-tag">&lt;<span class="hljs-title">div</span> <span class="hljs-attribute">class</span>=<span class="hljs-value">"row"</span>&gt;</span>
